<table class=3D"header" width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" cellp=
adding=3D"0">
<tr>
<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Elon Musk attention auction (1)</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">You could have a model of Elon Musk that is li=
ke:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">He runs a bunch of different companie=
s and owns large stakes in each of them.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom:=
 5px;">They all nominally do different things =E2=80=94=C2=A0cars, rockets,=
 tunnels, brain implants, artificial intelligence, complaining on the inter=
net =E2=80=94=C2=A0but there is a lot of overlap. Most of them=C2=A0employ =
engineers=C2=A0who move somewhat fungibly among companies, and most of them=
 seem to have big plans for artificial intelligence.</li>=09<li style=3D"ma=
rgin-bottom: 5px;">Each time he comes up with a value-creating idea, he can=
 more or less freely choose which company to implement it at.</li>=09<li st=
yle=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">He is motivated by money.</li>=09<li style=3D"m=
argin-bottom: 5px;">Therefore, he=C2=A0should implement the idea at the com=
pany that maximizes its contribution to his net worth.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I am not saying this is a particularly good mo=
del. Step 4, in particular, is suspect; Musk seems to have a lot of non-eco=
nomic motivations.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But let=E2=80=99s say this is your model. Now =
assume that Musk has some really good artificial intelligence=C2=A0idea tha=
t can create a lot of value and that can be implemented in any one of his c=
ompanies. Where should he do it? He should do it wherever it will most incr=
ease his net worth. This means maximizing:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">The scale of the company. Doing an ide=
a at a big company will probably have more impact than doing it at a little=
 company; doubling the value of a $200 billion company is worth more than d=
oubling the value of a $10 billion company. Plausibly =C2=A0=E2=80=9CAI, bu=
t put it in a car=E2=80=9D could create more value at Tesla Inc. than =E2=
=80=9CAI, but bury it underground=E2=80=9D would create at The Boring Co.<a=
 class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-1" style=3D"color: #000000; tex=
t-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-colo=
r: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transpa=
rent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a>
</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">His ownership of the company. Doi=
ng an idea at a=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/cli=
ck/35536316.258326/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIw=
MjQtMDUtMjMvc3BhY2V4LWNvbnNpZGVyaW5nLXRlbmRlci1vZmZlci10by1ib29zdC12YWx1ZS1=
0by0yMDAtYmlsbGlvbj9jbXBpZD1CQkQwNTI5MjRfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYW=
lsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yNDA1MjkmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vb=
mV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBcf4cc5d4" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemsc=
ope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoratio=
n: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000;=
 border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">$200 billion company<=
/a> where he owns 42% might create more value=C2=A0<em>for him=C2=A0</em>th=
an doing it at a $560 billion company where he owns 13%.<a class=3D"footnot=
e-index" href=3D"#footnote-2" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: non=
e !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; borde=
r-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transparent !important; =
display: inline-block;">
<span>[2]</span>
</a>
</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">The company=E2=80=99s=C2=A0<em>ab=
ility=C2=A0</em>to do the thing without raising outside capital (and, thus,=
 diluting him). Some of Musk=E2=80=99s companies generate cash, others cons=
ume it, and you can=E2=80=99t move money freely between them.</li>=09<li st=
yle=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">His ability, beyond formal ownership stakes, to=
 extract value from the company.=C2=A0Musk owns a relatively slim 13% of Te=
sla, but sometimes he goes to Tesla=E2=80=99s board of directors and says =
=E2=80=9Chi I would like $50 billion=E2=80=9D and they say =E2=80=9Cyes her=
e you go,=E2=80=9D though that mechanism may have stopped working.=C2=A0</l=
i>
</ul>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And you sort of multiply those numbers togethe=
r and pick the highest result.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you are an=C2=A0<em>investor=C2=A0</em>in t=
he broad <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35536316.=
258326/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYXhpb3MuY29tLzIwMjMvMTIvMzAvZWxvbi1tdXNrLXRlc2xhLXNw=
YWNleC10d2l0dGVyLTIwMjQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB00a9d526" itemprop=3D"Stor=
yLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; t=
ext-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-co=
lor: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Elon Mus=
k complex</a>, what do you do with this model? Possibly you diversify your =
bets across all of the Musk companies, as a lot of Musk investors seem to d=
o. Or possibly you try to pick a winner: You try to buy a big stake in the =
Musk company that you think will attract his best ideas, based on the crite=
ria above.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One odd thing that this means is that you have=
 some incentive to maximize valuation. Ordinarily, if you are an investor i=
n a company, you want to invest at a low valuation, so that you have more u=
pside. But if Elon Musk comes to you to raise money for a venture, and the =
venture has a valuation of $5 billion, maybe you should say no: Doubling th=
e value of a $5 billion company just won=E2=80=99t move the needle on Elon =
Musk=E2=80=99s personal wealth, so he has no incentive to pay any attention=
 to a $5 billion company. Or rather, you should not say no; you should say =
=E2=80=9Csure I=E2=80=99m in but at a $20 billion valuation,=E2=80=9D to at=
 least make it somewhat worth his while.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Again, this is all stupid and not a good model=
 of Elon Musk. He has tons of non-economic motivations, and also some track=
 record of taking companies from zero to hundreds of billions of dollars.=
=C2=A0Still. The=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/cl=
ick/35536316.258326/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS90ZWNoL2FpL2Vsb24tbXVza3MteGF=
pLXdpbGwtcmFpc2UtNi1iaWxsaW9uLWluLWxhdGVzdC1mdW5kcmFpc2luZy1yb3VuZC1mY2RkNz=
IyZD9tb2Q9aXRwX3dzag/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBe0d4925c" itemprop=3D"StoryLi=
nk" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text=
-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color=
: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Wall Street=
 Journal reports</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Elon Musk=E2=80=99s xAI said it raised $6 bill=
ion in its latest fundraising round, as the OpenAI rival looks to invest mo=
re in research and development amid fierce competition in the burgeoning se=
ctor.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The funding round brings the valuation of the =
year-old startup to $24 billion, including the newly raised funds, making i=
t the second-most valuable AI startup outside of OpenAI.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The money will be used to take =E2=80=9CxAI=E2=
=80=99s first products to market, build advanced infrastructure and acceler=
ate research and development of future technologies,=E2=80=9D xAI said.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The round is double the initial target set by =
Musk=E2=80=99s team. Investors had been talking about raising $3 billion at=
 an $18 billion valuation, including the new cash, The Wall Street Journal =
reported last month. Musk=E2=80=99s team raised the target in light of stro=
ng demand, according to people familiar with the matter.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Investors in the round include brand-name Sili=
con Valley firms such as Sequoia Capital and Andreessen Horowitz as well as=
 Valor Equity Partners, Vy Capital, Fidelity Management &amp; Research, and=
 Saudi Prince al-Waleed bin Talal and Kingdom Holding, xAI said on its webs=
ite late Sunday.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A lot of those names are familiar from Musk=E2=
=80=99s deal to buy Twitter. Maybe they hoped that Musk would do his AI stu=
ff at Twitter/X, but I suppose you have to hedge that bet. Also arguably a =
fresh $24 billion startup is a better place to capture Musk=E2=80=99s atten=
tion than a somewhat troubled social media site with a <a href=3D"https://l=
ink.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35536316.258326/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cudGhlZ3=
VhcmRpYW4uY29tL3RlY2hub2xvZ3kvMjAyNC9qYW4vMDIveC10d2l0dGVyLXN0b2NrLWZhbGxzL=
WVsb24tbXVzaw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBf9f18cbd" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" ite=
mscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decora=
tion: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #0000=
00; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">declining valuatio=
n</a>. Arguably this investment is a bet that xAI is likely to be the targe=
t of Musk=E2=80=99s attention for the next year or two, and the most import=
ant asset, in the Elon Musk corporate complex, is Musk=E2=80=99s attention.=
<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-3" style=3D"color: #000000; t=
ext-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-co=
lor: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: trans=
parent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[3]</span>
</a></p>
