, for a while, the richest person in the world; surely he has some sentimen=
tal attachment to it.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">It=E2=80=99s=
 still, by a significant margin, his=C2=A0<em>biggest=C2=A0</em>company, wh=
ich means that it has more ability to say =E2=80=9Csure here you go here=E2=
=80=99s $50 billion=E2=80=9D than, say, Boring Co. does.</li>=09<li style=
=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">It=E2=80=99s his only public company, which means =
that it is his most liquid asset: When he needed $44 billion to buy Twitter=
 Inc., the natural move was to sell and borrow against his Tesla shares, be=
cause those were the easiest things to turn into money.=C2=A0</li>
</ul>
