=E2=80=99t allow individual shareholders to vote in U.S. proxy elections=E2=
=80=94a common policy for financial institutions in the region. Last Monday=
, she posted and reposted 38 times, including instructions on voting at ban=
ks in Switzerland, Belgium and Sweden, and condemnation for a bank in the U=
.K. that reiterated that it doesn=E2=80=99t support voting.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">That bank =E2=80=9Cdoesn=E2=80=99t seem to car=
e to lose customers,=E2=80=9D she wrote on X. =E2=80=9CUnbelievable.=E2=80=
=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Obviously Tesla is the most attractive investm=
ent opportunity in the Musk universe=C2=A0<em>for retail investors</em>, be=
cause it=E2=80=99s the only one you can buy on the stock exchange. But for =
institutions the problem seems harder.=C2=A0</p>
<table class=3D"header" width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" cellp=
adding=3D"0">
<tr>
<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Gamma squeeze</h2>
</td>
</tr>
